                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>According to the Log, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_842">p.
                        842</ref>, Roosevelt and Churchill held discussions during the afternoon of
                    August 19 before they met with the Combined Chiefs of Staff. No record of the
                    discussion has been found. At one of their meetings on August 19, however,
                    Roosevelt and Churchill signed the “Articles of Agreement Governing
                    Collaboration Between the Authorities of the <gloss target="#t_USA1"
                        >U.S.A.</gloss> and the U.K. in the Matter of <gloss target="#t_TubeAlloys1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tube Alloys</hi>
                    </gloss>”. See <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1117">p.
                    1117</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
